This involves image processing and computer vision techniques, making cs.CV the most likely category. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with embedding a full-size secret image into a container image, which is a common technique used in multimedia applications. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper proposes a steganalysis technique that can be used to evaluate the security level of an arbitrary embedded-based digital watermarking or a steganography algorithm. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses a deep neural network for decoding the approximate estimate of the secret image. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a steganalysis technique that uses a deep neural network and generative adversarial networks, which are both subfields of artificial intelligence.
